The new map of the CD (Czech railways) less trains for roughly the same fare.
The Czech railways stopped or restricted from 13 December some less full speed and local trains, other links will be strengthened.
The whole transport volume will be reduced from the day of the new road map compared with today at two percent.
Most tariffs incl. Basic and Kundenfahrtarif will not be changed.
Several link opportunities in the capital, for example, the inhabitants of the Ostrava region, the railways, for this line of type Pendolino trains.
The train will no longer to Bratislava (the) .
Less fast trains will also be on the Prague - Pisek, Budweis, in principle, the direct links from Prague to Letohrad.
The biggest reduction in the railways in the district of Hradec Kralove (King Graz) , for a total of eight per cent, against a rise in Prague and environment.
Be lifted two night trains on the route from Prague Tabor - Budweis and on some days in the week of the operation of some fast trains on the route from Prague Pisek - reduced.
One of the biggest changes include the introduction of the new Direktverkehrsweges from milo vice to Prague, now, the inhabitants of Milovice in Lysa nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth route of suburban transport system Esko, whose opening thanks to the rail electrification from Lysa nad Labem after Milovice is possible.
The long - distance routes in the capital will be in the target station Prague - the main railway station.
The CD is more lines SC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and the trains after Sumperk/Jesenik in the space of two hours.
With the Pendolino passengers since 13 December no longer go to Bratislava.
This year's bill for regional rail: increase of 200 million
The fast trains are ordered and paid for by the Department of Transport, as a whole, the railway to reimburse the so - called liquidity loss in the next year, four billion kronor, genaus this year. local trains supply the districts, they have to pay for the next year, eight billion kronor, while the state three billion.
This year, the regional trains 200 million Czech crowns more expensive.
