The news of the arrest was first reported Friday night by the New York Times.
The new US policy stresses that the United States will provide a return if the Cuban government is taking concrete steps in this direction, such as the release of political prisoners and create more space for opposition.
Mobile phones and notebooks in Cuba are legal, even though they are new and coveted products in a country where the average earnings of a government employees is $15 per month.
The Cuban government allowed ordinary citizens only since this year, the purchase of a mobile phone, they will be used for the sending of text messages, as a 15 - minute telephone conversation a day would cost.
The Internet use is restricted on the island.
It is in expensive hotels and for foreign visitors and some government agencies, such as universities, accessible.
Cubans who want to connect to the government, often have their names.
Too many websites is restricted access.
In Cuba, the arrest of an American is rare.
Most of the few US citizens in Cuba are in prison for crimes such as drug smuggling, said Gloria Berbena, the press spokesman for the US representation in Havana.
Berbena said she could give no further information on the arrest.
The arrest and detention are clearly wrong.
