The average score of white Viertklässler from Washington D. C. in the last two years of 262 to 270 (on a scale of 500) , their African - American counterparts, but only three points from 209 to 212.
In reality, the performance gap between 2007 and 2009 from 53 to 58 points.
The progress of the African - American Achtklässler remained essentially the same, he fell a statistically negligible point of 245 to 244.
The average score of white pupils was not included in the test data, because the sample size was not big enough.
The picture over a six - year period is not encouraging.
