Managers revolution or the end of the Strategic early education?
If nothing changes in the leadership of the major French companies, our fight for the development of economic intelligence in vain ...
For over a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies in relation to his staff, said the position of the consumer from the marketing revolution: it is to join the staff " values " for the best, as it was earlier in the consumer products of the technicians in the station.
By the customer in the heart of the company has the marketing revolution the strategies of the conquest of the markets in the ground ... although the authoritarian temptation products separate factors preferences of customers to impose regularly again!
A demobilisation of staff can lead to a deadly demoralisation.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much larger phenomenon, especially the employees affected.
These demobilisation has a negative impact on the development of all intellectual functions of the company, in particular those of F, even more importantly, to those of economic intelligence.
In fact, the IU (Intelligence Economique = economic intelligence) " by all parties involved (...) a proactive approach and a forward - looking vision "; by the staff of a deployment, which the instructions of the authoritarian management.
We therefore call for an occupational revolution, which would be the staff at the heart of the concerns of the company on an equal footing with the customers.
The very - related benefits of internal polls
The internal polls, as the questionnaire, the Orange has made his wage earners, this revolution in relation to the management practice?
I fear that, unfortunately, not.
- First, because I could see that the whole structure with a new situation after many detours, finally, to do ... what it has always done.
Also because the authoritarianism - one of the pathologies of power in proportion to the importance of his own failures.
And finally, because most leaders a very simplified view of human behavior.
Emerged from the great engineering schools is their interpretation of the psychology mechanistic.
They play by intellectual comfort the old behavioristische theory, which was recently by the US " neuroscience " and unknowingly far - reaching research institutes and through the media.
Thus, and it suggests that it is possible, the " leverage " (sic) on the involvement of employees, a aktuellein Le Figaro. fr published by Ipsos poll in a position to a mechanistic control system, which is unsuitable for today's world.
The mobilisation factors identify and measure
Instead, a necessary for the smooth functioning of the modern business the adoption of a final view of human behavior.
It is, in any idea or practice of management to integrate a fundamental record: for wage - earners is the commitment to the company will only be possible if it is clearly as a means to achieve a portion of their dreams, their ambition and their projects.
Currently only the studies from the multifunctional analysis of this conception of the motivation of the staff.
These studies have shown that their companies on the basis of a Doxa judge them by their perceived image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life goals.
Thanks to the identification and the measurement of these factors can predict the executives of the companies ' social services ", and anticipate and their human resource management back to the right place.
So they create a fertile ground for the coordinated development of a robust and efficient economic intelligence.
