Drivers: three marathon for an agreement that ensures the supply of Christmas
After a three - week negotiating marathon, the unions of road Association and the the only employers ' organisation, which remained until the end - on Friday evening to reach an agreement, the strike order and the threat of an end to Christmas.
The signature meeting on Friday evening, " welcomed " the responsible for the transport minister Dominique Bussereau the agreement, which was launched on Wednesday morning after several weeks of negotiations.
After a second night of negotiations, the Verhandelnden on early Friday morning in the hope to sign the agreement at the end of the morning.
And although the three employers ' associations (FNTR, Unostra and OTRE) had left the meeting.
However, it has taken more than six hours from the start of the meeting at 11:00 a. m. until the conclusion of the agreement and only at m., the agreement was signed.
The conflict " would have the company very much harm " and " it was a fear that the holidays at the end of the year, " Bussereau.
The agreement provides for a wage increase of 4% for the lowest wages (local and regional road transport) and 2.9% for the highest wage groups (international transport) .
The hourly rate for workers with the lowest wages rise from 8.72 on 9.06 euros.
" It is not very much, but once we start small, " Patrice Clos (FO) .
The activists are now instructed not to block the supply centers.
" it will probably always be some recalcitrant who are not satisfied with the agreement, " he added.
The TLF - chairman Philippe Grillot spoke of a " good agreement ", although it was difficult to give these wage increases in the face of international competition ".
According to him, the increase in 170 euros a month for the low and 100 to 120 euros for the high wages.
" This agreement is based on the common sense and respect for the employees, " maxim Dumont (CFDT) , while Thierry Douine (CFTC) of " a historic agreement ".
Richard Jaubert (CGT) on this matter, " an acceptable compromise. "
The agreement also provides for an increase in the cost of travel by 3% and the upholding of the overall budget for road transport in the first half of 2010, which will allow it, in particular, the issue of monthly salary and the modernisation of the collective agreements.
M. Bussereau recalled that " the sinking of the burden on the employers to the tune of 100 million was the subject of an amendment to the government the corrected finances for 2009, which was adopted during the night from Thursday to Friday by the National Assembly.
The government calls " an identical " vote by the Senate.
The signature of the TLF allows that the agreement for the first of this organisation affiliated companies, and then in the event of an extension by the minister for the entire profession.
This will be the case " in a very short period of time ", Bussereau.
The opposition of the employers ' associations can only delay the process.
The federation FNTR lambasted a " fraudulent trading ", because the 100 million euro " were the sector to offset a portion of the carbon tax has already been promised. "
The secretary of state for transport forced us to negotiate as soon as possible, but not on the basis of a joint analysis, but the bird - eaters in the approaching Christmas days, laments the Unostra.
For the association Otre threatens the agreement " small and medium - sized companies in the sector over the next 12 months, a lot of digging. "
