Studies will entrümpelt
Partial success for the students: After a year of education strike drew the Culture Ministers of the countries on Thursday a: at a meeting of Ministers of Education and university rectors conference, both sides agreed to try to improve conditions in the Bachelor and master.
The students should be able to complete their studies.
In particular, they agreed to reduce the testing burden: in principle should each study only with a single test.
Moreover, the workload of the students and " a realistic and reasonable ".
Politics and universities also want the recognition of audit services between the universities inside and outside Germany.
The countries committed themselves to common structural targets for Bachelor and Masters more flexible.
Different countries regulations should not be beyond.
Less tests
Since the start of the student protests in June, Culture Minister and Uni rector the saying of the better Studierbarkeit in the mouth.
Now, for the first time, it was filled with a specific content.
The so - called accreditation Council decided to reduce the number of audits in part: " Each module includes usually with only one test, " it says in a 30 - page document, which is intended to regulate the authorisation of courses in part.
With the " significant reduction of the last review, " said the Accreditation Council chairman Reinhold Grimm, should be offered a " trend, the Studierbarkeit significantly disrupted. "
Moreover, the " Studierbarkeit " in the future, " the decisive criterion " in the design.
Modules as content are " strictly to examine " whether " unnecessary Einengungen of students in the choice of
Events " would be avoided.
The students ' right to maintain margins, the own initiative and promote ".
The rules should apply to the approval of new, but also in the review of existing studies.
This must all five years ' reakkreditiert " - which means that it will take until 2015, all the courses were reviewed.
Responsible for ten accreditation agencies, which are the accreditation, created by the countries.
The Culture Minister had urged the countries in October " with vigour " to the agencies that the material wealth is not too big and not too stringent verification regime.
In each, universities and colleges with the country's ministries have already agreed to take appropriate measures.
So far As the only country in Rhineland - Palatinate for the further development of the Bologna process additional funds.
The money should the universities, especially Tutorenprogramme set up and study advice and audit and strengthen.
Country and universities want to spend tens of millions of euros.
At the beginning of 2010, the government wants to introduce an amendment of the university law to parliament.
This is the conclusion of a study model only one test.
The study design should be more flexible, the recognition of certificates to other universities and facilitate access to the master.
By the end of next year, all courses in the country on their Studierbarkeit should be reviewed.
The government and opposition had argued on Thursday again on the study conditions in the country.
In addition to praise, there was also criticism of the decisions.
The federal Bureau of Juso - university groups called for the organisation of education policy should not be held behind closed doors, " the minister and university chancellors.
After the latest educational strikes should now also the students " have a say. "
Support the future graduates from the President of the university rectors ' Conference (HRK) , Margaret winter coat: " We need the experience of the students, " she said on Thursday in a meeting with the ministers, with which the HRK on a common reform paper.
The union education and science (GEW) the Bonn agreement as a whole does not go far enough: it calls for a legal right, each graduates with a Bachelor close access to a secondary Masters course.
On the other hand, countries must ensure that for the current generation of students Bachelor tomorrow sufficiently Masters with the best possible conditions available, so GEW board member Andreas cellar.
The countries need to hire more teachers.
At a freer access to the master, the Culture Minister said not, however.
More than a footnote to Herta Müller
