Dream worlds
Some people see in wachem state images and hear voices, others do not see or hear.
Not only in mental health and drug binge blurs the boundaries between fantasy and reality.
As long as it is happening in their sleep, everything is in order.
If we with closed eyes in our dark rooms, we must likes the wildest ideas and Phantasiegebilden.
Anyone who witnessed in a guard traumartige conditions, things, others do not see or hear, see and hear in the modern Western world as crazy or drug addicts, at least as Sonderling.
But such images and voices arise not only in mental health or drug binge.
Blame our imagination: the same neural processes that enable us to design houses, paint pictures or to write novels, sometimes to ensure that the boundaries between dream, fantasy and reality.
Traumartig changed awake awareness conditions can occur in many different forms, in the best case we call them visions, in the worst case of madness.
Although cause and effect may be different, the visions of the Mystikerin Hildegard of Bingen, the drug experiences of New Age prophet Carlos Castaneda, schamanische Entrückungszustände, psychosis and similar processes.
Hallucinations or delusions, if the balance of the neural messenger substances of the brain - especially dopamine, serotonin and noradrenaline, Acetylcholin - and the interaction of various parts of the brain is disrupted.
Complex hallucinations and wahnhafte thoughts are very often during a schizophrenic climate.
The force of gravity has no power over him
The connection of madness and dream, philosophers and doctors since ancient times.
Aristotle understood hallucinations as a form of the dream in the state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of the modern psychiatry, noted a " great similarity of mistaken one with a dream " for Sigmund Freud was the dream even " a climate of fear, with all the inconsistencies, Wahnbildungen, of such a ".
It is the autumn of 2001, when Henning T. in a comic figure.
His body is two dimensional and quietschbunt.
The gravity has no power more about him, he is hanging in the bedroom ceiling.
He senses a kick.
Behind him saying vicious form with blood red, distorted Fratzen, zähnefletschend.
They chase him him with serious, inflammatory boots, throwing him against the walls, he feels the pain of the whole body.
Noisy, malicious voices roar from walls and radio.
He can no longer tolerate it, the voices that attack and insult him.
Henning T. snaps two cable from the stereo, knotet a noose and fortified them in a hole in the ceiling.
He is rising on a loudspeaker and is tightening the noose around the neck.
Jumping.
The noose resolves itself.
This should be a lesson to you, the voices in trommelfellzerfetzendem chorus, " Walk in the clinic and let you cure! "
Today, Henning T. is 40 years old, he has six acute psychosis, the last 2 years ago, the first in nearly 20 years.
It was triggered by LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoaffektive - paranoid psychosis, moreover, he is bi - low, he takes medication to combat depression, mania, the schizophrenia.
He has learned to live with his illness, he is married for three years.
In the fears I have seen worst fear and deepest despair, he says.
The images are cruel reality
About one percent of the population at least once in a life with schizophrenia, in psychiatric hospitals, it is the second most common illness after the depression.
In an acute schizophrenic psychoses affected mostly can no longer distinguish between internal and external world, they are caught in a state to hallucinations, sizes, relationships or paranoia.
The vote is particularly widespread hearing voices, or comment on dialogisieren.
Optical hallucinations are not rare.
The person is not important to separate more trivial, the brain can no longer ausfiltern disturbing signals, the awareness is awash with impressions.
As the dream opens the psychosis the floodgates for a flood of ideas and fantasies, the deeper awareness classes.
The reality of perception in the climate is subjektzentriert, says Professor Thomas fox, head doctor of the clinic for General psychiatry in the Universitätsklinikum Heidelberg.
The Schizophrene finds itself in the middle of it, everything has a significance to him.
At the same time, he is in a passive role, he will, in the dream, overwhelmed by what has happened and
Schizophrenic often feel threatened, controlled and manipulated.
A reality is not possible, the medical images are cruel reality, excluded awakening.
Once in a lifetime to have experienced a Halluzination
Unlike in the dream, says fox, " but the sinnliche and spatial structure of reality, which is perceived in the psychosis, basically. "
The obsessive thoughts and hallucinations based in reality, the alienation of the Erlebens will take place in real terms.
Why is our brain antics, researchers still puzzle.
Exceptional conditions can lead to everyone that he loses the reality in the short - term, says fox.
But not everyone will develop a climate.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but twin studies have shown that the genes are not the only determinants.
Researchers assume that involved minimal brain damage.
We suspect that the neuronale maturation of the brain in an early stage of development, a viral infection of the mother during pregnancy, for example, fox explained.
But it remains a mystery, as the disruption of the neural system, the manifestiere not also first over many years.
Environmental factors also play a role - stress or traumatic experiences can be a trigger for psychosis, if the choice is there.
Also halluzinogene drugs can trigger psychosis, as they are in the central system.
If our brain is overheating
The nutcases, Psychotiker suffer from their hallucinations and swallow expensive drugs in order to get rid of them, others give money for drugs in order to get, says the Lübecker psychology professor Erich caste.
Whether fantasy as pleasant or unpleasant, is often just a matter of the position.
Box collects for ten years, reports of hallucinations and Trugerscheinungen, last year, he has his results in the book " The unreal world in our head.
Hallucinations are among the typical effects of psychosis, but also of astonishing many other diseases.
These include mental disorders, such as borderline or depression often diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis, Alzheimer's skull and brain trauma.
Surprisingly, under certain circumstances, even the brain healthy people.
Hallucinations, so castes, from memory content, which would normally be withheld.
They arise when, in which are processed sensory initially or too little; if our brains hot or even if stimulation.
Drugs can trigger this state as well as brain damage or a psychosis.
But also appeal of deprivation, stress, pain or other mental exceptional situations.
In recent studies, up to a third of the respondents to have experienced at least once in the life of a hallucinations.
In the summer of 2005, Sarah K. 16 years old, she lives in a small town in Mecklenburg - Western Pomerania and visited the school.
A normal girl, really.
If it were not for the images and voices.
In the break, it can happen that a schlaksiger boy with long, dark hair.
If he says, look at the classmates surprisingly - no one else sees or hears these boys.
They think the timid girl for a day, but Sarah K. not dreaming, it knows it.
She is awake, she hears and sees these boys, just as the girls in the bank and alongside it.
You can even feel his presence, at least for moments.
A pleasant feeling is that they may be the boys.
Am I crazy? , asks them sometimes.
But she knows that this boy and the other fantasy is not real, and then disappear again.
At night, the most frightening phenomena
The images are often also a burden.
If you are sitting in the class room, they can follow the teaching material sometimes, because the teachers in their eyes and ears just unveils a new classmates, while for all other hearing and visible on the table mathematical equations.
At night are the phenomena most frightening.
If they are in their dark room to sleep, which is far too little and far too late, they can often not distinguish whether she is awake or dreams, whether the pictures you see, the Fratzen or the girl with the bleeding wounds arms and legs, before their open or closed eyes.
Let me in, they are the characters.
Parents and friends told them nothing, which would be crazy.
Autumn 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
In the past year she has insisted the baccalaureate and lives with her friend.
A year ago, the hallucinations.
Since the Internet contact with the psychologists caste, she knows that she is not stupid.
Cow is also a work of art from despair
If someone is socially isolated or withdrawal is under appeal, he says, in all probability hallucinations, after a while.
I suspect that the brain is underemployed, and even for his entertainment.
Sarah K., a Einzelkind, had as a little girl, fear of other children, often played alone.
Their hallucinations began with 13, when they learned that the man they call dad, since they can think of, not their father.
As visual and acoustic hallucinations the same brain areas are active, the real impressions and sounds, it is affected as Sarah K. difficult to distinguish fantasy and reality. " Every experience, " says caste, " will take place in the brain, the reality is there.
Hallucinations are also images of the brain, that is why they are so real. "
Even late - night dream images of caste as a form of hallucinations.
The hallucinations of healthy do not differ fundamentally from those of an acute psychosis.
In contrast to schizophrenia are mentally healthy in the situation, their images as unreal.
Caste advises his patients, therefore, the hallucinations as a special ability.
Border state between dream and hallucinations
In our world too much bewusstseinszentrierten imaginary experience, unfortunately, says Michael Schmidt - Degenhard, professor in Heidelberg and chief doctor of the clinic for psychiatry and psychotherapy of Florence Nightingale hospital in Düsseldorf.
A psychosis is a serious, painful disease, but it also has positive, creative - is also a work of art from despair.
Schmidt - Degenhard has researched the so - called oneiroide experience form, a special form of traumartig modified guard awareness.
Oneiroide are highly complex, detailed quasi - dreams, the Erlebende for real, and he cannot distinguish downstream from the.
The oneiroide consciousness state in trauma or illness in extreme situations, for example, in Polyradikulitis patients full awareness of a motor paralysis.
If a person is threatened by loss of self - and by, for example, by world, he replaced the life - threatening reality through their own imaginary world, the reality is, says Schmidt Degenhard.
A kind of border state between dream and hallucinations.
Since the deal with a situation in the reality is not possible, a world of change will take place, but the real situation in the imagination.
An intensive form of good Foundation and meaning in an intolerable situation, which allows people to design their own ability, not in a loss of loss.
Everything is real, later in the memory
The devoted art historian Peter Cornelius Claussen describes his Oneiroid - experiences in his book " change of heart " as a bailout of the soul.
He is 49 years old when his consciousness after a heart valves operation, followed by a heart transplant on travel, while his body to the intensive care unit for Bewegungslosigkeit.
Claussen, a appears in a self - created world, other times and places: he is seen as bettlägerigen, old man, on board a Zugsanatoriums, a robot his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages of nobles who drugs from blood.
By a Greeks on the motorcycle in his own country, with his hospital bed in the Firnschnee the Alps and a Korean Mafioso.
He is completely in the imagined, everything is real, later in the memory.
These internal travel for Claussen differ radically from any dream.
Dream is a different state, he describes his experience.
In contrast, the memories from mental travel and even after years in the minor details.
More and more even than real memories.
The intensity of this experience goes beyond the horizon of our other secular life experience, says the psychiatrist Schmidt - Degenhard.
Ultimately, show Oneiroide psychoses, hallucinations and drugs binge, how fragile our internal figures of external reality in the guards.
Any change of status, say the psychologist caste, " can lead to a Verformung of what we call reality. "
An experience which may also be enriching.
