The promises of FonPeek
Peek is extremely limited, a device with which you can read his e - mails, without a chance to be able to see certain annexes or to surf the Internet.
It has enjoyed his five minutes of fame, as the magazine Time to one of the products of the year.
To see It is on the road, it is unlikely, but the idea is, nevertheless, especially for young people of interest.
In contrast to the Smartphones Peek costs very little and has a very favourable flat rate, for example, only half of the price of the flat rate of an iPhone.
After the company has seen the success that it has two new devices on the market: one, that is only intended for Twitter, the other with a lifelong free service for data, quite unlike the Peek, in which it must pay a six times higher.
Fonpeek, which was presented yesterday at the event, is the European version of this invention and thus its third version.
It has the same borders, as his American counterpart, however, has a surprise.
The monthly maintenance price for the phone, around 12 euros per month, roaming for the whole of Europe.
Those who travel with a Smartphone around the world, already know what it means to have to give up all the data in order to be able to read his e - mails, once you cross the border, or if you are desperately seeking a café with WIFI (or a link with Fon) .
The idea of roaming with flat rate is incredibly tempting and should actually be possible for a long time.
It is true that some telephone providers already offer specific contracts and prices for abroad, but in my experience, you need a doctorate in physics and a good glasses to read all the fine print.
The repeated criticism from the European Commission in relation to affordable roaming tariffs for the whole of Europe remained almost always ignored.
Outside of their own country, has always afraid to read his e - mails and rightly so.
That a small device as FonPeek (although it is always amazing that it has the name of Fon, although it has no Wifi/WLAN) this kind of tariffs, means that the telephone providers are slowly but surely to rethink and start to consider various ways of how they can use their data network.
Kindle is another good example, in its prices is the downloads of books and other questions on the Internet.
Without Vetrag and without snags.
It is an internetfähiges equipment and pay only once, at the time of purchase, and not every month.
And that is what I expect of a day of FonPeek a buying opportunity with lifelong Internet access as it offers the Peek already in the United States.
And that is not because I want to buy it.
I read my e - mails with the telephone, thank you.
But I expect this, because I believe that it would be a more appropriate model for the consumer.
It would be interesting to be able to see a computer with the same system.
