75% of working mothers have because of their maternity problems in the work
The discrimination in the work has increased in recent years, especially among the younger women who wish to have children.
This result is the CSIC in collaboration with the Institute for Women " fertility and career women in Spain. "
The survey of 9.737 women between 15 and 75 years leaves no doubt about it: 75% of working women see their career opportunities in the labour market because of their maternity.
The study is that there are major differences in the decision to start a family and the number of children, depending on whether the women work or not and if so, what kind of work they perform.
Those of you who work outside the home, no other activity, only part - time work or have no fixed contract, is more likely to be mothers and have more children.
By contrast, postpone the women with a solid job, particularly in the public sector, the creation of a family and motherhood and therefore have fewer children.
" The women in the age group between 35 and 49 years with a solid job get their first child on average only 3.7 years after the draw, a figure that rises to 4.1 years for women with jobs, which took longer to achieve this and and the first child until much later.
It also has the kind of work a great influence on motherhood, albeit less than the calendar in terms of preparedness, " explains the CSIC, Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor, the age of the women in the marriage and the first child to be taken into account.
According to the survey, the age at the time of the marriage and the first child the higher, the higher the level of education.
This difference was in the women of the same age.
For example, the women in the group between 35 and 49 years, depending on whether they are only the main education or higher education, on average, each with 25.1 or mother for the first time.
There is, depending on their level of education, another difference between the women.
While the women with Hauptschlussabschluss even before its first permanent employment and their first child, make it the women with a medium or high school exactly the other way around and find a permanent employment and marry later and then have their first child, Delgado.
