Cowardly aggression
My 70 - year - old mother was last week by our city in the town of Fuenlabrada, when suddenly a group of young people between 15 and 18 years alongside her and our dog, our dog is a Mischling, we have taken from the animal and just six kilos, and then out of the blue lost him two Fußtritte and injured him so hard.
Our outrage is not in words, because it is incomprehensible to us, where the fun in a cheap aggression against a small and which is, of course, to the leash.
In addition to the attack, a woman who was walking she wanted to see these people as a result of the incident, they feared for their own lives, because if a Wahnsinniger attacked a dog, he will be the same, perhaps with a woman, a child, an elderly gentleman or probably even with each, the weaker than he is.
The incident occurred in a normally quiet neighbourhoods at five o'clock in the afternoon on an ordinary Tuesday.
The dog has geheult all day long.
Of course, we have in a nahgelegenen police complaint, however, we have great doubts as to whether it will bring and to prevent any prejudice from the outset, we would just make it clear that the cowardly criminals were Spaniards.
Our indignation about what has happened has led us to this incident.
We cannot understand what must be in the minds of these young people that they find a cheap attack on a defenceless animal fun, an animal that we love, society and friendship.
We do not know where the good education and respect for the animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the Helms
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in cooperation with the Spanish Foundation for road safety (Fesvial) a campaign to promote the helmet use, especially among the younger motorcyclists, as both companies announced today.
This initiative is to draw attention to the importance of the helmet use, because it is ultimately the only protection element, the head injury or even death in the event of a motorcycle accident.
Michelin pointed out that this campaign is part of its commitment to the road safety, the " far more than just the design and manufacture of products, with every day more and more secure " and confirmed that they also help with other actions educational and informative nature to this objective every day to come a step closer.
This new campaign to promote the helmet use on the motorcycle, which, under the slogan ' to be or not to be ' is, in a first phase to distribute posters of 500 motorcycle workshops, in order to achieve the best possible spread.
Finally, Michelin stressed that the road safety " is a constant concern " of the company, and it is precisely for the reason that they are manufacturers of tyres for two - rädige vehicles are obliged to see that one of its main objectives of the development of safer products.
The sale of small trucks is rising again in
After nearly two years of the car market for small trucks finally some light at the end of the dark tunnel.
The 9.425 vehicles, which were approved in November in Spain, an increase of 12.6% in the year 2008, and, more importantly, they are the first increase even after 22 consecutive months will decline, according to the manufacturers ' association and the car dealers ' association Ganvam figures.
These good numbers, however, are currently only with great caution, as the reference data used for comparison in November 2008, which was a particularly bad Verkausjahr with a drop of 60% on the previous year.
However, we must remember that, apart from the increase in the last month, the overall approval of these 11 months still 40% below the sales figures of the previous financial year.
Since January, a total of 95.853 vehicles were sold in this number, but all vehicles, from which the vans market is: descendants of passenger cars, Pick - ups, vans, small vans and lighter chassis.
Furthermore, the same storm clouds in the sky, the most in demand, because even if some of the vehicles will be purchased by individuals, most of the sales to small and medium - sized enterprises, which almost 100% of all cases the purchase with a third - party financing.
So we have to these restrictions, which are the result of the supply to tap the credit institutions, there are other factors, such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic situation.
In this scenario, and unlike the cars, the financial support for the purchase of a vehicle of the plan 2000E little.
This plan, however, is not only to individuals, the self - employed and small businesses have a right to expect that, if they are up to 3.5 tonnes with a CO2 emissions, which 160 grams per want to buy, but the low sales figures speak for themselves.
Just yesterday had Ganvam reminded that it is part of the state, including a special attention to this small and, of course, also on the industrial vehicles (trucks and buses) .
The car dealers association predicts a similar for the 2010 year just as the last, for which it with a sales (in passenger cars and SUVs) by 19%.
The support for Bremsmanövern in critical situations is now duty
As was the Antiblockierbremssystem ABS and how it is now happening with the ESP stability control systems, the aid must be a duty on the brakes in European cars.
In fact, they are already duty all newly registered passenger cars and light trucks, for the remaining vehicles was set by the end of February 2011.
The measure adopted by the European Union aims to improve the protection of pedestrians, but these braking systems, because of their operation can also help to prevent many front - rear collisions.
The task of the Notbremsassistenten is more pressure on the brakes in the event of a critical braking maneuver, which recognises the system on the basis of the drivers said brake on the
However, this system is not the pressure until the end.
According to one of the components manufacturer for the Bosch vehicles, a third of the drivers involved in an accident before the collision even more on the brake pedal and half of them had not slowed down with full force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The Bremshilfe with maximum force in the braking system and reduce the time and therefore also the Bremsabstand, a car in the Bremsvorgang back.
According to a study by the EU could each year up to 1,100 fatal accidents involving pedestrians to damage, be prevented if all cars were equipped with this type of Notbremsassistenten.
It would be even less accidents - it is estimated that every fourth accident involving personal injury could be prevented, as soon as the so - called intelligent system popularity.
Then the vehicle is equipped with a system that (on radar or a camera) obstacles and warns the driver, while at the same time, there is a slight pressure on the brakes.
If the driver then responded, helps him the system to increase the pressure on the brake pedal, if it would be necessary.
If the driver does not react to the warning, and even if the collision was inevitable, the Bremsassistent the maximum pressure on the brakes in order to keep the damage as much as possible.
