New programmes for the evaluation of vehicles
In these days of storms and accidents not only deserve the motor workshops
Every day, thousands of vehicles were involved in an accident, in the garage, where a experts assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
Not a single accident is the same and the calculation of the cost of the parts and working hours can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair cost of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including the parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
It is, however, with the support of the latest computer tools a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of the experts use this type of systems.
The services and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs to collect the information they receive from the manufacturers to deal with them and their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, part of the American group Solera, the market leader; 80% of all with their products.
The other two companies, which compete with the Tool - market for evaluation and draw up a report, GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data, which the manufacturers, is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, sales manager of Audatex, with 63 manufacturers and importers, with each one of them the information in a different format.
In addition to the handling of data, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and Motorisierungen came on the market than in the years before.
As soon as a new car on the market, starting for the company's work.
It is a difficult task, because jedeseinzelnde of thousands and thousands of vehicles must be entered and share price.
In addition, each model of an " intelligent " Graphikbild on the different parts of the vehicle, " click on ".
If it is a great model is sold, the work can be completed in a week, if the procedure is moving quickly.
If it is a less gebräuchliches car, it can take up to three or four months. at present, Audatex in 99, 2% of Spain displaced on full information.
Among the more rarefied models they have, for example, information about the Porsche models, but not on Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In relation to the car park on the streets, over 99%.
For the implementation of the documentation and the production of databases, Audatex worldwide on eight (Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) distributed centres and each of them has to certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid) .
There are more than a hundred technicians (usually experts for engineering) simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invested 90 million euros per year in the preparation of these databases.
Every month, they take 2.5 million data on and their customers get the updates every second day.
The drafting of this enormous flow of information allows companies to use these in various ways and to offer different products.
The most common use is the use of the repairs and repair, but there are, depending on the country also tools for the management of scrap metal parts or for calculating the Feil or residual value of a car.
The only businesses that have a leader who is on the value of used cars in Spain, informed.
Audatex provides this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
In the testing of the products that can be easily an overview of the kind of support the industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, is the star of the products AudaPlus, a standard solution to Begutachutng of accidents for the judges.
It involves vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the estimated repair times by the manufacturer or the Lackierungspreise.
This Tool is depending on use, that is, for every opinion, paid.
The most expensive it will be for customers, it rarely, a maximum of ten times in the month, namely 5.75 per month.
Against any insurance company that carries out the thousands of opinions, the price with Audatex.
In other products, such as AudaVIN, can be a vehicle and equipment with which it ran from the installation band, only by the chassis number.
AudaGlass deals with the car windows, and AudaSubastas is a for the specialist market open service on the Internet, with the one for vehicles that have been declared a total loss, can offer.
The statistics service is very useful in identifying trends, the implementation of geodemographischen analyses or to receive information about the derogations for brand and model.
You can, for example, how many models of a particular car because of breakdowns in the garage or how many of them in a certain period of time were involved in a serious accident.
Gt motives is the only Spanish company, which is the development of this type of computer tools.
It sells, among other Gt Estimate, which is also intended for consultants and on the same kind of digital images, access to parts or prices and official working hours of the manufacturer.
Gt motives is a company of the group, which was founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions to the assessment of damage, breakdowns or Wartungen of vehicles.
The GT leaders for advice is a reference product on the market.
They work with 24,000 users in garages, 3,100 accountants and 53 insurance companies.
Their volume of business in the last three years, with 20% per year and 2008 the turnover of EUR 10.8 million.
At the beginning of last year, they began to go on the international market with the opening of an office in Paris.
Audatex was founded in Germany in 1966 and 1979 in Spain.
According to sources of the company, 62% of its business in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
The total turnover in the world of the group Solera (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex, ABZ, Hollander and IMS) amounts to $557 million more than in 2008.
Here the company has revenue of EUR 19.1 million, 7.2% more than in the previous year.
2005 was the group Solera in the stock market worth $1 billion and today their shares at a value of $2.4 billion.
Since 2007, they are on the New York Stock Exchange and part of the reference index Standard& Poor's.
Auction of accident cars on the Internet
